ICAP Will Exit U.K. Over EU Transactions Tax, Independent Says

-- B y   C a r o l i n e   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-08-21T10:03:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/icap-will-exit-u-k-over-eu-transactions-tax-independent-says.html
ICAP Plc (IAP) , a U.K. interdealer broker,
will leave the U.K. if the European Union endorses Franco-German
plans for a tax on financial transactions, the  Independent on
Sunday  reported, citing an interview with chief executive,
 Michael Spencer .  Spencer added that it would be “economic suicide” if the
U.K. agreed to the tax and said it would “destroy the city of
 London ,” the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Caroline Alexander in London at 
 calexander1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  